  "title": "Migration Planner-SK",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Develop and execute Python scripts to automate processes, manipulate data, and support network operations, demonstrating technical proficiency and innovation.</li><li>Design, read, and interpret scripts that generate network device configurations to ensure accurate and efficient network deployment.</li><li>Apply expertise in IP networking, VLANs, QoS, and broadband access technologies (DSL, GPON, Ethernet) to support and optimize network infrastructure.</li><li>Plan, schedule, and sequence large-scale technical operations to ensure timely and coordinated execution of network projects.</li><li>Analyze large datasets to identify trends, troubleshoot issues, and support decision-making for network performance improvements.</li><li>Communicate effectively with technical and operational teams to facilitate collaboration and ensure alignment on project goals and execution.</li><li>Adapt to working in customer data center environments and manage responsibilities within shift-based or scheduled maintenance settings, including nights and weekends.</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma in Engineering (Telecommunication, IT or equivalent)</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Portfolio or examples of relevant Python programming work demonstrating automation and scripting capabilities</li></ul><p>Work Location- Near Tai Seng MRT<br />Contract Duration- 9 months<br />Prior experience in data centre environment would be an added advantage.<br />Someone with basic IT skills and good communication skill will be good fit.</p>",
